On the hook — the simple Dune-level one:
Dune's hook in one sentence: A messiah is the most dangerous thing humanity can create.
Yours, based on everything you've actually built: Power doesn't corrupt. Loss does.
That's it. That's the simple version. Every character in your story is defined not by what they wanted but by what they lost and what they became in the space that loss created. Conq lost his twin, his father, his mother, his arm, his brother. The sister lost her family, her childhood, her choice. Stabilizer lost his identity when he learned his bloodline. The dead twin lost her life and then lost her humanity climbing back from it. The fatherless daughter lost her name, her place, her people.
